# Meme-to-Money — UI/UX High-Level Document

> This doc covers **UI flows & screens** for the Meme-to-Money app (Mini YouTube for memes & short videos). Each screen lists components, interactions, and backend integration.

---

## 1. Auth & Onboarding

**Screens:**

* **Splash Screen** → app logo, quick loading animation.
* **Login Screen** → fields (email/username, password), social login (Google/Apple), CTA button.
* **Signup Screen** → fields (username, email, password, confirm password), optional referral code.
* **Forgot Password Screen** → email input, reset link trigger.
* **KYC Onboarding (creators only)** → upload ID doc, selfie verification, status pending.

**Interactions:**

* Tap login/signup buttons → API call (`POST /auth/login`, `POST /auth/register`).
* Social login → token exchange with backend.
* KYC submit → `POST /users/:id/kyc`.

---

## 2. Main Feed (Memes + Short Videos)

**Screens:**

* **Vertical feed** → memes/images (tap-to-expand) + autoplay short videos (muted).
* **Engagement bar** → like, comment, share, tip, save.
* **Native ads** → shown after every N content pieces.

**Interactions:**

* Vertical swipe → load next/previous content.
* Tap like/comment → `POST /content/:id/engage`.
* Tap tip → open tip modal → `POST /wallet/tip`.
* Long press on content → report menu → `POST /content/:id/report`.

---

## 3. Upload Flow

**Screens:**

* **Upload type selection** → choose Meme (image/GIF) or Video (≤60s).
* **Editor screen** → add caption, hashtags, tags, preview.
* **Upload progress screen** → progress bar, success/failure message.

**Interactions:**

* Select file → request upload URL (`GET /upload-url`).
* Upload → multipart upload to S3/CDN.
* Submit → `POST /content` with metadata.

---

## 4. Profile & Wallet

**Screens:**

* **Profile screen** → avatar, bio, follower/following counts, content grid.
* **Creator dashboard** → stats (views, tips, ad share), earnings chart.
* **Wallet screen** → coin balance, tip history, buy coins, withdraw button.

**Interactions:**

* Tap edit profile → `PATCH /users/:id`.
* Tap buy coins → payment SDK → `POST /wallet/buy`.
* Tap withdraw → `POST /payouts/request`.

---

## 5. Search & Discovery

**Screens:**

* **Search bar** → input text.
* **Trending screen** → hashtags, creators, popular memes/videos.
* **Search results** → content grid/list.

**Interactions:**

* Enter search term → `GET /search?q=` (Elastic).
* Tap hashtag/creator → open filtered feed/profile.

---

## 6. Brand Campaigns

**Screens:**

* **Campaigns list** → active sponsored challenges.
* **Campaign detail** → rules, prizes, entries.
* **Submit entry** → attach meme/video to campaign.

**Interactions:**

* Tap join → `POST /campaigns/:id/entries`.
* Campaign feeds → filtered via `GET /campaigns/:id/entries`.

---

## 7. Moderation & Reports

**Screens:**

* **Report modal** → reason dropdown, submit button.
* **Moderation queue (admin only)** → list flagged content.

**Interactions:**

* Tap report → `POST /content/:id/report`.
* Admin approve/remove → `PATCH /content/:id/status`.

---

## 8. Navigation Model

* Bottom nav bar: **Feed | Search | Upload | Wallet | Profile**
* Top nav bar: logo, notifications, settings.

---

## 9. Integration Hooks Summary

* Auth → User Service
* Upload & Content → Content Service
* Wallet/Coins → Monetization Service
* Ads/Challenges → Ad Service
* Feed & Trending → Analytics/Feed Service

---

## 10. Next Steps

1. Wireframe each screen (low-fidelity sketches).
2. Create UI component library (buttons, forms, feed cards, modals).
3. Connect Figma or Canva mockups to backend API references.
